  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Building Agroecological Production Alternatives and Strengthening the Organization of Families Affected and Threatened by Dam Construction</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will be implemented in the Southern and Northeastern regions where families have either resettled because of dam construction, or stayed on the edges of hydropower reservoirs and other dams. The project will work to guarantee food security and sovereignty and consolidate pilot experiences in agroecological production with 41 families. Another 750 families will receive training and education in agroecology and other production models. Passing on knowledge and exchanging experiences will benefit 1,480 additional families. This project will also support public policy advocacy and defense for rights of people affected by dams by training 180 leaders from the two regions.</narrative>
  </description>
